text: Tynada was a town of ancient Pisidia, inhabited during Roman times. Its name does not occur in ancient authors, but is inferred from epigraphic and other evidence. Its site is located near Terziler Sivrisi in Asiatic Turkey. ==References== Category:Populated places in Pisidia Category:Former populated places in Turkey Category:Roman towns and cities in Turkey Category:History of Isparta Province
title: Tynada
